data.title: Baked Fresh Daily
data.text: We could not resist stopping in for a cappuccino mid morning.  Once inside we could not resist the selections in the pastry case.  My husband ordered the chocolate eclair and I had the cream puff.  OMG If I closed my eyes I surely would be in France.  The quality was that good.  Treat yourself by stopping in at the French Pastry Shop.  You won't be disappointed.  PS:  Our cappuccino's were twice the size you get in Europe.

data.title: truly a blessing, a haven, an oasis, a trip to France
data.text: I cannot tell you how very much I love this place, a true home, a shelter, a wonderful place for an early continental breakfast with a divine cafe au lait (even with the soymilk I requested) and a perfectly freshly baked crunchy externally, soft internally, baguette. The greatest and most touching joy for me was for the first time in decades to find native Francophones deigning to share their BELLE LANGUE with me, now clumsily, but delighted. A perfect place, also for lunch. I tried their soup fo the day (lentil) which was wonderful and warming on a chilly day, as well as their immense ratatouille crepe. I asked for a half baguette turkey and Swiss Cheese sandwich for the road, and they graciously included a packet of DIJON MUSTARD (OMG!) and the mayonnaise on the side, which I forfeited. To end my light lunch, being my birthday, I requested a Mille Feuille (Napoleon) which was everything it should and must be, as it is, most truly. Je vous remercie beaucoup, French Pastry Shop, for all of your generous kindness and graciousness for this lost wanderer, a moment a la maison. Merci.

data.title: Cash ONLY - don't forget!
data.text: This is a super quaint and authentic bakery - physically part of the La Fonda Hotel. Excellent pastries and sandwiches - but CASH ONLY. I learned the hard way - lol

data.title: Tourist trap, avoid if you want quality food and coffee
data.text: I ordered a spinach crepe here and was served something I would not even feed to my dog.  It was a crepe for sure, but the filling was made from frozen, chopped spinach and some bland cream sauce.  Also it was about a pound of filling, which is just way too much.  A spinach crepe should have fresh spinach with identifiable cheese layered inside.  What a huge disappointment.  The coffee was absolutely terrible as well, I am not blaming the roaster, a lot of bad coffee comes down to execution.  I do not recommend this place at all.

data.title: Lovely cosy winter brunch
data.text:
Very cute and cosy French Pastry Shop! Perfect crepes with fresh fruits and fast, friendly service! Well deserved certificate of excellence :)
Will definitely come again!

data.title: French Pastry Shop & Restaurant was a pleasant surprise in the middle of tourist center
data.text: After walking the area touring, the French Pastry Shop & Restaurant was a pleasant surprise to find right in the middle of the tourist area.  We were hungry and it smelled good the moment we entered.  It was busy so the service was slow.  The restroom, which is very clean is nearby to use!  We didn't try any pastries on this visit but it sure smelled good.

data.title: Breakfast X 2
data.text: A birthday celebration and later in the week a walk down memory lane.  George, the owner made our wedding cake to order - a Black Forest Cake which was my father-in-law's favorite.  Everyone still talks about "that cake."  It was amazing.  This visit we actually managed to see George and say hello.  As tourists  now we don't always arrive early enough to catch up.

data.title: Lunch
data.text: Had lunch with wife and daughter.  I enjoyed several light pastries - all filling and tasty.  Both girls enjoyed quiche.  We arrived just in time to beat the lunch rush, but noticed many to go orders .  A little pricey but that makes for a better vacation.

data.title: Food was ok
data.text: Had lunch today. I had a Ratatouille crêpe with dinner salad and my wife had a grilled Swiss cheese with a mocha. The mocha was very chocolatey and well made. The salad greens were fresh. The crepe and sandwich were average at best. The crepe was too firm.

data.title: Total surprise and delight....
data.text: This was such a surprise but did see it was very highly rated in the past. The quality and richness of all of the desserts/dishes needs to be experienced...we went back four times while we stayed in Santa Fe.

data.title: Delicious and Friendly Service
data.text: This well-located shop and restaurant provides delicious and heart food, and the staff is very friendly, fast, and helpful.

data.title: Fantastic Restaurant!
data.text: I highly recommend going to this place. Great pastries and crepes. This place only takes cash so come prepared with cash but worth the effort.

data.title: Get elastic pants
data.text: Some of the best pastries I have eaten.  Many will look good until you bite into them, but these tasted as good as they looked.  The best Napoleon I have had in years. Flaky crust and creamy filling, noting was soggy on it.  Cookies were heaven balls of coconut. Everything we tasted was really good. They accept cash only so go prepared.

data.title: Close to the Plaza
data.text: We stopped here for a quick snack while walking around the Santa Fe Plaza area.  The cream puff we shared was delicious!  The coffee was very strong, I guess I should have expected that at a French pastry shop :)

data.title: Don't bother
data.text:
You would think that a French Pastry shop would be able to produce a decent crepe, but our recent experience this week proved that assumption to be wrong. 
The two crepes we ordered were inedible, unless you were starving, and a disgrace to the image of French cooking. 
The savory crepe, egg and bacon, was NOT savory, and I had to ask for something to make it more flavorful, and was brought a small bowl of very hot chili which was too spicy for my pepper-tolerant palate and which my wife could not even tolerate with a tiny quantity.
The obscene crepe was the peach crepe (we were notified by the waitress that the peaches were canned), but all that they did was place the peach halves inside a too-thick crepe envelope without any attempt to add a filling or make the peach halves smaller and more edible.
We were dismayed and left 3/4 of each crepe on our plates to be thrown in the trash where they belonged.

data.title: Excellent start for your day
data.text: I noticed another reviewer indicated lackluster service.  Our experience could not have been more opposite.  Our waitress was very attentive to our table, and constantly checked with us about our coffee and our needs.  My husband and I both started with crepes...he had the spinach and cheese and I had the chicken mushroom with béchamel.  Both were excellent!  My crepe was filled with chicken.  Of course we could not leave the French Bakery without a pastry treat!  Again, so good...and pretty as a picture.  Breakfast here was not inexpensive...but it would not have been so high if we had just had our crepes and left without the pastries;  but it IS vacation...and the gorgeous pastries beckoned us.  We thoroughly enjoyed our time here.  And, by the way...excellent coffee!

data.title: Nice Breakfast Option
data.text:
We had crepe and a quiche. Both were surprisingly large portions and very good, although the quiche wasn't quite warm all the way through.
Cash only service, no credit cards.
It's in the same building as a large hotel, with on-street entry, so doesn't seem to be a part of it.

data.title: No place was open for breakfast
data.text: Traveling from the East Coast means you are up early and looking for coffee or something to eat.  This was one of the few places open for business.  The service was lackluster - slow and unenthusiastic.  The coffee was passable.  The pastries were okay

data.title: Great eats
data.text: The location and food were excellent. The prices reasonable. Waitress not friendly or helpful at all, but other guests and regulars were helpful with menu suggestions. Need to bring cash! No credit cards or checks accepted!

data.title: A good but pricey little French bakery.
data.text: This cash-only eatery located at the La Fonda on the Plaza is actually a pretty realistic Patisserie/Boulangerie. Everything is a bit pricey, as you would expect for a tourist area, but the crepes and pastries were about as good as you'll find in France. We enjoyed our stop for a sweet treat.
